OpenVPN SNI Bypass for Keenetic v1.1
=====================================

SNI Host: play.googleapis.com
TLS Support: 1.0, 1.1, 1.2, 1.3
SSH Port: 222

Features:
- Automatic SNI bypass with play.googleapis.com
- Full TLS 1.3 support with modern cipher suites
- Backward compatible with TLS 1.0/1.1/1.2
- Packet fragmentation for DPI bypass
- Stunnel integration for TCP connections
- Automatic configuration processing

Installation:
1. Copy package to modem:
   scp -P 222 openvpn-sni-bypass_1.1-1_all.ipk admin@192.168.1.1:/tmp/

2. SSH to modem:
   ssh -p 222 admin@192.168.1.1

3. Install package:
   opkg update
   opkg install /tmp/openvpn-sni-bypass_1.1-1_all.ipk

Usage:
1. Configure OpenVPN from Keenetic Web UI as normal
2. SNI bypass will be applied automatically
3. TLS 1.3 support is enabled by default

Management Commands:
- Status: /opt/etc/init.d/S25openvpn-sni status
- Start: /opt/etc/init.d/S25openvpn-sni start
- Stop: /opt/etc/init.d/S25openvpn-sni stop
- Restart: /opt/etc/init.d/S25openvpn-sni restart

Logs:
- Main log: /var/log/openvpn-sni.log
- Stunnel log: /var/log/stunnel-openvpn.log
- System log: logread | grep openvpn-sni

Troubleshooting:
1. Check if stunnel is running:
   ps | grep stunnel

2. Test TLS connection:
   openssl s_client -connect play.googleapis.com:443 -tls1_3

3. View detailed logs:
   tail -f /var/log/openvpn-sni.log
   tail -f /var/log/stunnel-openvpn.log

Uninstall:
opkg remove openvpn-sni-bypass

Support:
- Check OpenVPN status from Keenetic Web UI
- All configurations are processed automatically
- Original configs are preserved

Cipher Suites (TLS 1.3):
- TLS_AES_256_GCM_SHA384
- TLS_CHACHA20_POLY1305_SHA256
- TLS_AES_128_GCM_SHA256

Cipher Suites (TLS 1.0-1.2):
- ECDHE-RSA-AES256-GCM-SHA384
- ECDHE-RSA-CHACHA20-POLY1305
- ECDHE-RSA-AES128-GCM-SHA256
- DHE-RSA-AES256-GCM-SHA384
- And more...